-- Swiss Stocks Advance on European Commission Bank-Aid Call
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-05-30T11:52:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/swiss-stocks-advance-on-european-commission-bank-aid-call.html
Swiss stocks advanced after the
European Commission called for direct euro-area aid for troubled
banks and touted common bond issuance as an antidote to the debt
crisis now threatening to overwhelm  Spain .  The Swiss Market Index rose 0.4 percent to 5,939.71 at 1:50
p.m. in Zurich. The broader Swiss Performance Index added 0.3
percent today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tom Stoukas at 
